Shareholders of  Nigeria â€™s  United
Bank for Africa Plc (UBA)  approved a plan to become a financial
services holding company, Punch  reported , citing proceedings at
a court-ordered meeting of the lender.  Under the new structure, UBA will remain listed on the
 Nigerian Stock Exchange , while existing shareholders will cede
60 percent of their stake in UBA Plc for 100 percent ownership
of UBA Holdings Plc, the Lagos-based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
